column8: What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Isolation of human @GeneSrc$ and its binding specificity with @GeneTgt$.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] We screened proteins for interaction with @GeneSrc$, and cloned the full-length cDNA of human @GeneTgt$, which encoded 1225 amino acids.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Yeast two-hybrid assay, GST binding assay and immunoprecipitation demonstrated that delta-catenin interacted with a hydrophilic loop region in the endoproteolytic C-terminal fragment of @GeneSrc$, but not with that of @GeneTgt$.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Yeast two-hybrid assay, GST binding assay and immunoprecipitation demonstrated that @GeneSrc$ interacted with a hydrophilic loop region in the endoproteolytic C-terminal fragment of @GeneTgt$, but not with that of PS-2.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Yeast two-hybrid assay, GST binding assay and immunoprecipitation demonstrated that @GeneSrc$ interacted with a hydrophilic loop region in the endoproteolytic C-terminal fragment of PS1, but not with that of @GeneTgt$.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] These results suggest that @GeneSrc$ and @GeneTgt$ partly differ in function.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] We also found another @GeneSrc$, @GeneTgt$, interacted with PS1.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] We also found another armadillo-protein, @GeneSrc$, interacted with @GeneTgt$.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] We also found another @GeneSrc$, p0071, interacted with @GeneTgt$.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Activation of @GeneSrc$ng factor mediated by @GeneTgt$beta converting enzyme</T4>.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The @GeneSrc$ converting enzyme (ICE) processes the inactive @GeneTgt$ precursor to the proinflammatory cytokine.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The @GeneSrc$ converting enzyme (@GeneTgt$) processes the inactive IL-1beta precursor to the proinflammatory cytokine.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The interleukin-1beta (IL-1beta) converting enzyme converting enzyme (@GeneSrc$) processes the inactive @GeneTgt$ precursor to the proinflammatory cytokine.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] @GeneSrc$ was also shown to cleave the precursor of interferon-gammagamma inducing factor</T12> (@GeneTgt$) at the authentic processing site with high efficiency, thereby activating IGIF and facilitating its export.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] @GeneSrc$ was also shown to cleave the precursor of interferon-gammagamma inducing factor</T12> (IGIF) at the authentic processing site with high efficiency, thereby activating @GeneTgt$ and facilitating its export.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] ICE was also shown to cleave the precursor of @GeneSrc$gamma inducing factor</T12> (@GeneTgt$) at the authentic processing site with high efficiency, thereby activating IGIF and facilitating its export.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Interferon-gamma and @GeneSrc$ were diminished in the sera of @GeneTgt$-/- mice exposed to Propionibacterium acnes and lipopolysaccharide.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] Involvement of @GeneSrc$ signal transducer gp130 in @GeneTgt$-mediated signal transduction.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] @GeneSrc$ is a novel cytokine with a variety of biofunctions which overlap with those of @GeneTgt$.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] We have previously identified @GeneSrc$ specific binding protein which is distinct from that of @GeneTgt$ in a number of cell lines.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The similarities in biofunctions and differences in ligand binding proteins between @GeneSrc$ and IL-6 prompted us to investigate whether IL-11 shares common signal transduction mechanisms with @GeneTgt$.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The similarities in biofunctions and differences in ligand binding proteins between IL-11 and @GeneSrc$ prompted us to investigate whether IL-11 shares common signal transduction mechanisms with @GeneTgt$.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] We have examined early signals triggered by @GeneSrc$ or @GeneTgt$ in a multifactor-dependent human erythroleukemic cell line, TF-1.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The results showed that @GeneSrc$ and IL-6 can both stimulate cell proliferation, induce similar pattern of protein tyrosine phosphorylation, and activate the same proto-oncogene (@GeneTgt$) expression in TF-1 cells.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The results showed that IL-11 and @GeneSrc$ can both stimulate cell proliferation, induce similar pattern of protein tyrosine phosphorylation, and activate the same proto-oncogene (@GeneTgt$) expression in TF-1 cells.

What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] The results showed that @GeneSrc$ and @GeneTgt$ can both stimulate cell proliferation, induce similar pattern of protein tyrosine phosphorylation, and activate the same proto-oncogene (junB) expression in TF-1 cells.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] These findings imply that IL-11 and @GeneSrc$ share similar early signaling events with the possibility of using the same signal transducer, @GeneTgt$.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] These findings imply that @GeneSrc$ and @GeneTgt$ share similar early signaling events with the possibility of using the same signal transducer, gp130.
What is [AIMED] ? [SEP] These findings imply that @GeneSrc$ and IL-6 share similar early signaling events with the possibility of using the same signal transducer, @GeneTgt$.
